<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">115. Cennini, Cennino D’Andrea. The Craftsman’s Handbook. Translated by Daniel V. Thompson, Jr. New Haven, Connecticut: Yale University Press , 1933. Reprint, Dover, n.d.. 142 pp. Index, endnotes/footnotes, B/W illus. </p><p class="annot">Medieval materials and techniques for painting and applied arts.are described in a well-documented survey. Written in the fifteenth century, this work was first printed in Rome in 1821 and translated into several languages throughout the nineteenth century. </p></div>
